 33 /***
 34 * Invoke the named method on each element in the array
 35 * and return a new array containing the results of the invocation.
 36 *
 37 <code><pre>
 38   [1.1, 2.2, 3.3, 4.4].invoke("floor")
 39   => [1, 2, 3, 4]
 40 
 41   ['hello', 'world', 'cool!'].invoke('substring', 0, 3)
 42   => ['hel', 'wor', 'coo']
 43 </pre></code>
 44 *
 45 * @param {String} method The name of the method to invoke.
 46 * @param [arg...] Optional arguments to pass to the method being invoked.
 47 *
 48 * @type Array
 49 * @returns A new array containing the results of invoking the
 50 * named method on each element.
 51 */
 52 Array.prototype.invoke = function(method) {
 53   var args;
 54   args = __slice.call(arguments, 1);
 55   return this.map(function(element) {
 56     return element[method].apply(element, args);
 57   });
 58 };
 59 /***
 60 * Randomly select an element from the array.
 61 *
 62 * @returns A random element from an array
 63 */
 64 Array.prototype.rand = function() {
 65   return this[rand(this.length)];
 66 };
 67 /***
 68 * Remove the first occurance of the given object from the array if it is
 69 * present.
 70 *
 71 * @param {Object} object The object to remove from the array if present.
 72 * @returns The removed object if present otherwise undefined.
 73 */
 74 Array.prototype.remove = function(object) {
 75   var index;
 76   index = this.indexOf(object);
 77   return index >= 0 ? this.splice(index, 1)[0] : undefined;
 78 };
 79 /***
 80 * Returns true if the element is present in the array.
 81 *
 82 * @param {Object} element The element to check if present.
 83 * @returns true if the element is in the array, false otherwise.
 84 * @type Boolean
 85 */
 86 Array.prototype.include = function(element) {
 87   return this.indexOf(element) !== -1;
 88 };
 89 /***
 90  * Call the given iterator once for each element in the array,
 91  * passing in the element as the first argument, the index of
 92  * the element as the second argument, and this array as the
 93  * third argument.
 94  *
 95  * @param {Function} iterator Function to be called once for
 96  * each element in the array.
 97  * @param {Object} [context] Optional context parameter to be
 98  * used as `this` when calling the iterator function.
 99  *
100  * @returns `this` to enable method chaining.
101 */
102 Array.prototype.each = function(iterator, context) {
103   var _len, _ref, element, i;
104   if (this.forEach) {
105     this.forEach(iterator, context);
106   } else {
107     _ref = this;
108     for (i = 0, _len = _ref.length; i < _len; i++) {
109       element = _ref[i];
110       iterator.call(context, element, i, this);
111     }
112   }
113   return this;
114 };
115 Array.prototype.eachWithObject = function(object, iterator, context) {
116   this.each(function(element) {
117     return iterator.call(context, object, element);
118   });
119   return object;
120 };
121 Array.prototype.eachSlice = function(n, iterator, context) {
122   var i, len;
123   if (n > 0) {
124     len = (this.length / n).floor();
125     i = -1;
126     while (++i < len) {
127       iterator.call(context, this.slice(i * n, (i + 1) * n), i * n, this);
128     }
129   }
130   return this;
131 };
132 /***
133  * Returns a new array with the elements all shuffled up.
134  *
135  * @returns A new array that is randomly shuffled.
136  * @type Array
137 */
138 Array.prototype.shuffle = function() {
139   var shuffledArray;
140   shuffledArray = [];
141   this.each(function(element) {
142     return shuffledArray.splice(rand(shuffledArray.length + 1), 0, element);
143   });
144   return shuffledArray;
145 };

164 /***
165  * Returns an object containing the extremes of this array.
166  * <pre>
167  * [-1, 3, 0].extremes() # => {min: -1, max: 3}
168  * </pre>
169  * @param {Function} [fn] An optional funtion used to evaluate
170  * each element to calculate its value for determining extremes.
171  * @returns {min: minElement, max: maxElement}
172  * @type Object
173 */
174 Array.prototype.extremes = function(fn) {
175   var max, maxResult, min, minResult;
176   fn || (fn = function(n) {
177     return n;
178   });
179   min = (max = undefined);
180   minResult = (maxResult = undefined);
181   this.each(function(object) {
182     var result;
183     result = fn(object);
184     if (typeof min !== "undefined" && min !== null) {
185       if (result < minResult) {
186         min = object;
187         minResult = result;
188       }
189     } else {
190       min = object;
191       minResult = result;
192     }
193     if (typeof max !== "undefined" && max !== null) {
194       if (result > maxResult) {
195         max = object;
196         return (maxResult = result);
197       }
198     } else {
199       max = object;
200       return (maxResult = result);
201     }
202   });
203   return {
204     min: min,
205     max: max
206   };
207 };
208 /***
209  * Pretend the array is a circle and grab a new array containing length elements.
210  * If length is not given return the element at start, again assuming the array
211  * is a circle.
212  *
213  * @param {Number} start The index to start wrapping at, or the index of the
214  * sole element to return if no length is given.
215  * @param {Number} [length] Optional length determines how long result
216  * array should be.
217  * @returns The element at start mod array.length, or an array of length elements,
218  * starting from start and wrapping.
219  * @type Object or Array
220 */
221 Array.prototype.wrap = function(start, length) {
222   var end, i, result;
223   if (typeof length !== "undefined" && length !== null) {
224     end = start + length;
225     i = start;
226     result = [];
227     while (i++ < end) {
228       result.push(this[i.mod(this.length)]);
229     }
230     return result;
231   } else {
232     return this[start.mod(this.length)];
233   }
234 };
235 /***
236  * Partitions the elements into two groups: those for which the iterator returns
237  * true, and those for which it returns false.
238  * @param {Function} iterator
239  * @param {Object} [context] Optional context parameter to be
240  * used as `this` when calling the iterator function.
241  *
242  * @type Array
243  * @returns An array in the form of [trueCollection, falseCollection]
244 */
245 Array.prototype.partition = function(iterator, context) {
246   var falseCollection, trueCollection;
247   trueCollection = [];
248   falseCollection = [];
249   this.each(function(element) {
250     return iterator.call(context, element) ? trueCollection.push(element) : falseCollection.push(element);
251   });
252   return [trueCollection, falseCollection];
253 };
254 /***
255  * Return the group of elements for which the return value of the iterator is true.
256  *
257  * @param {Function} iterator The iterator receives each element in turn as
258  * the first agument.
259  * @param {Object} [context] Optional context parameter to be
260  * used as `this` when calling the iterator function.
261  *
262  * @type Array
263  * @returns An array containing the elements for which the iterator returned true.
264 */
265 Array.prototype.select = function(iterator, context) {
266   return this.partition(iterator, context)[0];
267 };
268 /***
269  * Return the group of elements that are not in the passed in set.
270  *
271  * @param {Array} values List of elements to exclude.
272  *
273  * @type Array
274  * @returns An array containing the elements that are not passed in.
275 */
276 Array.prototype.without = function(values) {
277   return this.reject(function(element) {
278     return values.include(element);
279   });
280 };
281 /***
282  * Return the group of elements for which the return value of the iterator is false.
283  *
284  * @param {Function} iterator The iterator receives each element in turn as
285  * the first agument.
286  * @param {Object} [context] Optional context parameter to be
287  * used as `this` when calling the iterator function.
288  *
289  * @type Array
290  * @returns An array containing the elements for which the iterator returned false.
291 */
292 Array.prototype.reject = function(iterator, context) {
293   return this.partition(iterator, context)[1];
294 };
295 Array.prototype.inject = function(initial, iterator) {

297     return (initial = iterator(initial, element));
298   });
299   return initial;
300 };

522 /**
523 The Core class is used to add extended functionality to objects without
524 extending the object class directly. Inherit from Core to gain its utility
525 methods.
526 
527 @name Core
528 @constructor
529 
530 @param {Object} I Instance variables
531 */
532 Core = function(I) {
533   var self;
534   I || (I = {});
535   return (self = {
536     I: I,
537     /**
538     Generates a public jQuery style getter / setter method for each
539     String argument.
540 
541     @name attrAccessor
542     @methodOf Core#
543     */
544     attrAccessor: function() {
545       var attrNames;
546       attrNames = __slice.call(arguments, 0);
547       return attrNames.each(function(attrName) {
548         return (self[attrName] = function(newValue) {
549           if (typeof newValue !== "undefined" && newValue !== null) {
550             I[attrName] = newValue;
551             return self;
552           } else {
553             return I[attrName];
554           }
555         });
556       });
557     },
558     /**
559     Generates a public jQuery style getter method for each String argument.
560 
561     @name attrReader
562     @methodOf Core#
563     */
564     attrReader: function() {
565       var attrNames;
566       attrNames = __slice.call(arguments, 0);
567       return attrNames.each(function(attrName) {
568         return (self[attrName] = function() {
569           return I[attrName];
570         });
571       });
572     },
573     /**
574     Extends this object with methods from the passed in object. `before` and
575     `after` are special option names that glue functionality before or after
576     existing methods.
577 
578     @name extend
579     @methodOf Core#
580     */
581     extend: function(options) {
582       var afterMethods, beforeMethods;
583       afterMethods = options.after;
584       beforeMethods = options.before;
585       delete options.after;
586       delete options.before;
587       $.extend(self, options);
588       if (beforeMethods) {
589         $.each(beforeMethods, function(name, fn) {
590           return (self[name] = self[name].withBefore(fn));
591         });
592       }
593       if (afterMethods) {
594         $.each(afterMethods, function(name, fn) {
595           return (self[name] = self[name].withAfter(fn));
596         });
597       }
598       return self;
599     },
600     include: function(Module) {
601       return self.extend(Module(I, self));
602     }
603   });

605 var DebugConsole;
606 DebugConsole = function() {
607   var REPL, container, input, output, repl, runButton;
608   REPL = function(input, output) {
609     var print;
610     print = function(message) {
611       return output.append($("<li />", {
612         text: message
613       }));
614     };
615     return {
616       run: function() {
617         var code, result, source;
618         source = input.val();
619         try {
620           code = CoffeeScript.compile(source, {
621             noWrap: true
622           });
623           result = eval(code);
624           print(" => " + (result));
625           return input.val('');
626         } catch (error) {
627           return error.stack ? print(error.stack) : print(error.toString());
628         }
629       }
630     };
631   };
632   container = $("<div />", {
633     "class": "console"
634   });
635   input = $("<textarea />");
636   output = $("<ul />");
637   runButton = $("<button />", {
638     text: "Run"
639   });
640   repl = REPL(input, output);
641   container.append(output).append(input).append(runButton);
642   return $(function() {
643     runButton.click(function() {
644       return repl.run();
645     });
646     return $("body").append(container);
647   });

649 Function.prototype.withBefore = function(interception) {
650   var method;
651   method = this;
652   return function() {
653     interception.apply(this, arguments);
654     return method.apply(this, arguments);
655   };
656 };
657 Function.prototype.withAfter = function(interception) {
658   var method;
659   method = this;
660   return function() {
661     var result;
662     result = method.apply(this, arguments);
663     interception.apply(this, arguments);
664     return result;
665   };

901 (function() {
902   var Matrix, Point;
903   /***
904    * Create a new point with given x and y coordinates. If no arguments are given
905    * defaults to (0, 0).
906    * @name Point
907    * @param {Number} [x]
908    * @param {Number} [y]
909    * @constructor
910   */
911   Point = function(x, y) {
912     return {
913       /***
914        * The x coordinate of this point.
915        * @name x
916        * @fieldOf Point#
917       */
918       x: x || 0,
919       /***
920        * The y coordinate of this point.
921        * @name y
922        * @fieldOf Point#
923       */
924       y: y || 0,
925       /***
926        * Adds a point to this one and returns the new point.
927        * @name add
928        * @methodOf Point#
929        *
930        * @param {Point} other The point to add this point to.
931        * @returns A new point, the sum of both.
932        * @type Point
933       */
934       add: function(other) {
935         return Point(this.x + other.x, this.y + other.y);
936       },
937       /***
938        * Subtracts a point to this one and returns the new point.
939        * @name subtract
940        * @methodOf Point#
941        *
942        * @param {Point} other The point to subtract from this point.
943        * @returns A new point, this - other.
944        * @type Point
945       */
946       subtract: function(other) {
947         return Point(this.x - other.x, this.y - other.y);
948       },
949       /***
950        * Scale this Point (Vector) by a constant amount.
951        * @name scale
952        * @methodOf Point#
953        *
954        * @param {Number} scalar The amount to scale this point by.
955        * @returns A new point, this * scalar.
956        * @type Point
957       */
958       scale: function(scalar) {
959         return Point(this.x * scalar, this.y * scalar);
960       },
961       /***
962        * Determine whether this point is equal to another point.
963        * @name equal
964        * @methodOf Point#
965        *
966        * @param {Point} other The point to check for equality.
967        * @returns true if the other point has the same x, y coordinates, false otherwise.
968        * @type Boolean
969       */
970       equal: function(other) {
971         return this.x === other.x && this.y === other.y;
972       },
973       /***
974        * Calculate the magnitude of this Point (Vector).
975        * @name magnitude
976        * @methodOf Point#
977        *
978        * @returns The magnitude of this point as if it were a vector from (0, 0) -> (x, y).
979        * @type Number
980       */
981       magnitude: function() {
982         return Point.distance(Point(0, 0), this);
983       },
984       /***
985        * Calculate the dot product of this point and another point (Vector).
986        * @name dot
987        * @methodOf Point#
988        *
989        * @param {Point} other The point to dot with this point.
990        * @returns The dot product of this point dot other as a scalar value.
991        * @type Number
992       */
993       dot: function(other) {
994         return this.x * other.x + this.y * other.y;
995       },
996       /***
997        * Calculate the cross product of this point and another point (Vector).
998        * Usually cross products are thought of as only applying to three dimensional vectors,
999        * but z can be treated as zero. The result of this method is interpreted as the magnitude
1000        * of the vector result of the cross product between [x1, y1, 0] x [x2, y2, 0]
1001        * perpendicular to the xy plane.
1002        * @name cross
1003        * @methodOf Point#
1004        *
1005        * @param {Point} other The point to cross with this point.
1006        * @returns The cross product of this point with the other point as scalar value.
1007        * @type Number
1008       */
1009       cross: function(other) {
1010         return this.x * other.y - other.x * this.y;
1011       },
1012       /***
1013        * The norm of a vector is the unit vector pointing in the same direction. This method
1014        * treats the point as though it is a vector from the origin to (x, y).
1015        * @name norm
1016        * @methodOf Point#
1017        *
1018        * @returns The unit vector pointing in the same direction as this vector.
1019        * @type Point
1020       */
1021       norm: function() {
1022         return this.scale(1.0 / this.length());
1023       },
1024       /***
1025        * Computed the length of this point as though it were a vector from (0,0) to (x,y)
1026        * @name length
1027        * @methodOf Point#
1028        *
1029        * @returns The length of the vector from the origin to this point.
1030        * @type Number
1031       */
1032       length: function() {
1033         return Math.sqrt(this.dot(this));
1034       },
1035       /***
1036        * Computed the Euclidean between this point and another point.
1037        * @name distance
1038        * @methodOf Point#
1039        *
1040        * @param {Point} other The point to compute the distance to.
1041        * @returns The distance between this point and another point.
1042        * @type Number
1043       */
1044       distance: function(other) {
1045         return Point.distance(this, other);
1046       }
1047     };
1048   };
1049   /***
1050    * @param {Point} p1
1051    * @param {Point} p2
1052    * @type Number
1053    * @returns The Euclidean distance between two points.
1054   */
1055   Point.distance = function(p1, p2) {
1056     return Math.sqrt(Math.pow(p2.x - p1.x, 2) + Math.pow(p2.y - p1.y, 2));
1057   };
1058   /***
1059    * Construct a point on the unit circle for the given angle.
1060    *
1061    * @param {Number} angle The angle in radians
1062    * @type Point
1063    * @returns The point on the unit circle.
1064   */
1065   Point.fromAngle = function(angle) {
1066     return Point(Math.cos(angle), Math.sin(angle));
1067   };
1068   /***
1069    * If you have two dudes, one standing at point p1, and the other
1070    * standing at point p2, then this method will return the direction
1071    * that the dude standing at p1 will need to face to look at p2.
1072    * @param {Point} p1 The starting point.
1073    * @param {Point} p2 The ending point.
1074    * @returns The direction from p1 to p2 in radians.
1075   */
1076   Point.direction = function(p1, p2) {
1077     return Math.atan2(p2.y - p1.y, p2.x - p1.x);
1078   };
1079   /***
1080    * <pre>
1081    *  _        _
1082    * | a  c tx  |
1083    * | b  d ty  |
1084    * |_0  0  1 _|
1085    * </pre>
1086    * Creates a matrix for 2d affine transformations.
1087    *
1088    * concat, inverse, rotate, scale and translate return new matrices with the
1089    * transformations applied. The matrix is not modified in place.
1090    *
1091    * Returns the identity matrix when called with no arguments.
1092    * @name Matrix
1093    * @param {Number} [a]
1094    * @param {Number} [b]
1095    * @param {Number} [c]
1096    * @param {Number} [d]
1097    * @param {Number} [tx]
1098    * @param {Number} [ty]
1099    * @constructor
1100   */
1101   Matrix = function(a, b, c, d, tx, ty) {
1102     a = (typeof a !== "undefined" && a !== null) ? a : 1;
1103     d = (typeof d !== "undefined" && d !== null) ? d : 1;
1104     return {
1105       /***
1106        * @name a
1107        * @fieldOf Matrix#
1108       */
1109       a: a,
1110       /***
1111        * @name b
1112        * @fieldOf Matrix#
1113       */
1114       b: b || 0,
1115       /***
1116        * @name c
1117        * @fieldOf Matrix#
1118       */
1119       c: c || 0,
1120       /***
1121        * @name d
1122        * @fieldOf Matrix#
1123       */
1124       d: d,
1125       /***
1126        * @name tx
1127        * @fieldOf Matrix#
1128       */
1129       tx: tx || 0,
1130       /***
1131        * @name ty
1132        * @fieldOf Matrix#
1133       */
1134       ty: ty || 0,
1135       /***
1136        * Returns the result of this matrix multiplied by another matrix
1137        * combining the geometric effects of the two. In mathematical terms,
1138        * concatenating two matrixes is the same as combining them using matrix multiplication.
1139        * If this matrix is A and the matrix passed in is B, the resulting matrix is A x B
1140        * http://mathworld.wolfram.com/MatrixMultiplication.html
1141        * @name concat
1142        * @methodOf Matrix#
1143        *
1144        * @param {Matrix} matrix The matrix to multiply this matrix by.
1145        * @returns The result of the matrix multiplication, a new matrix.
1146        * @type Matrix
1147       */
1148       concat: function(matrix) {
1149         return Matrix(this.a * matrix.a + this.c * matrix.b, this.b * matrix.a + this.d * matrix.b, this.a * matrix.c + this.c * matrix.d, this.b * matrix.c + this.d * matrix.d, this.a * matrix.tx + this.c * matrix.ty + this.tx, this.b * matrix.tx + this.d * matrix.ty + this.ty);
1150       },
1151       /***
1152        * Given a point in the pretransform coordinate space, returns the coordinates of
1153        * that point after the transformation occurs. Unlike the standard transformation
1154        * applied using the transformPoint() method, the deltaTransformPoint() method
1155        * does not consider the translation parameters tx and ty.
1156        * @name deltaTransformPoint
1157        * @methodOf Matrix#
1158        * @see #transformPoint
1159        *
1160        * @return A new point transformed by this matrix ignoring tx and ty.
1161        * @type Point
1162       */
1163       deltaTransformPoint: function(point) {
1164         return Point(this.a * point.x + this.c * point.y, this.b * point.x + this.d * point.y);
1165       },
1166       /***
1167        * Returns the inverse of the matrix.
1168        * http://mathworld.wolfram.com/MatrixInverse.html
1169        * @name inverse
1170        * @methodOf Matrix#
1171        *
1172        * @returns A new matrix that is the inverse of this matrix.
1173        * @type Matrix
1174       */
1175       inverse: function() {
1176         var determinant;
1177         determinant = this.a * this.d - this.b * this.c;
1178         return Matrix(this.d / determinant, -this.b / determinant, -this.c / determinant, this.a / determinant, (this.c * this.ty - this.d * this.tx) / determinant, (this.b * this.tx - this.a * this.ty) / determinant);
1179       },
1180       /***
1181        * Returns a new matrix that corresponds this matrix multiplied by a
1182        * a rotation matrix.
1183        * @name rotate
1184        * @methodOf Matrix#
1185        * @see Matrix.rotation
1186        *
1187        * @param {Number} theta Amount to rotate in radians.
1188        * @param {Point} [aboutPoint] The point about which this rotation occurs. Defaults to (0,0).
1189        * @returns A new matrix, rotated by the specified amount.
1190        * @type Matrix
1191       */
1192       rotate: function(theta, aboutPoint) {
1193         return this.concat(Matrix.rotation(theta, aboutPoint));
1194       },
1195       /***
1196        * Returns a new matrix that corresponds this matrix multiplied by a
1197        * a scaling matrix.
1198        * @name scale
1199        * @methodOf Matrix#
1200        * @see Matrix.scale
1201        *
1202        * @param {Number} sx
1203        * @param {Number} [sy]
1204        * @param {Point} [aboutPoint] The point that remains fixed during the scaling
1205        * @type Matrix
1206       */
1207       scale: function(sx, sy, aboutPoint) {
1208         return this.concat(Matrix.scale(sx, sy, aboutPoint));
1209       },
1210       /***
1211        * Returns the result of applying the geometric transformation represented by the
1212        * Matrix object to the specified point.
1213        * @name transformPoint
1214        * @methodOf Matrix#
1215        * @see #deltaTransformPoint
1216        *
1217        * @returns A new point with the transformation applied.
1218        * @type Point
1219       */
1220       transformPoint: function(point) {
1221         return Point(this.a * point.x + this.c * point.y + this.tx, this.b * point.x + this.d * point.y + this.ty);
1222       },
1223       /***
1224        * Translates the matrix along the x and y axes, as specified by the tx and ty parameters.
1225        * @name translate
1226        * @methodOf Matrix#
1227        * @see Matrix.translation
1228        *
1229        * @param {Number} tx The translation along the x axis.
1230        * @param {Number} ty The translation along the y axis.
1231        * @returns A new matrix with the translation applied.
1232        * @type Matrix
1233       */
1234       translate: function(tx, ty) {
1235         return this.concat(Matrix.translation(tx, ty));
1236       }
1237     };
1238   };
1239   /***
1240    * Creates a matrix transformation that corresponds to the given rotation,
1241    * around (0,0) or the specified point.
1242    * @see Matrix#rotate
1243    *
1244    * @param {Number} theta Rotation in radians.
1245    * @param {Point} [aboutPoint] The point about which this rotation occurs. Defaults to (0,0).
1246    * @returns
1247    * @type Matrix
1248   */
1249   Matrix.rotation = function(theta, aboutPoint) {
1250     var rotationMatrix;
1251     rotationMatrix = Matrix(Math.cos(theta), Math.sin(theta), -Math.sin(theta), Math.cos(theta));
1252     if (typeof aboutPoint !== "undefined" && aboutPoint !== null) {
1253       rotationMatrix = Matrix.translation(aboutPoint.x, aboutPoint.y).concat(rotationMatrix).concat(Matrix.translation(-aboutPoint.x, -aboutPoint.y));
1254     }
1255     return rotationMatrix;
1256   };
1257   /***
1258    * Returns a matrix that corresponds to scaling by factors of sx, sy along
1259    * the x and y axis respectively.
1260    * If only one parameter is given the matrix is scaled uniformly along both axis.
1261    * If the optional aboutPoint parameter is given the scaling takes place
1262    * about the given point.
1263    * @see Matrix#scale
1264    *
1265    * @param {Number} sx The amount to scale by along the x axis or uniformly if no sy is given.
1266    * @param {Number} [sy] The amount to scale by along the y axis.
1267    * @param {Point} [aboutPoint] The point about which the scaling occurs. Defaults to (0,0).
1268    * @returns A matrix transformation representing scaling by sx and sy.
1269    * @type Matrix
1270   */
1271   Matrix.scale = function(sx, sy, aboutPoint) {
1272     var scaleMatrix;
1273     sy = sy || sx;
1274     scaleMatrix = Matrix(sx, 0, 0, sy);
1275     if (aboutPoint) {
1276       scaleMatrix = Matrix.translation(aboutPoint.x, aboutPoint.y).concat(scaleMatrix).concat(Matrix.translation(-aboutPoint.x, -aboutPoint.y));
1277     }
1278     return scaleMatrix;
1279   };
1280   /***
1281    * Returns a matrix that corresponds to a translation of tx, ty.
1282    * @see Matrix#translate
1283    *
1284    * @param {Number} tx The amount to translate in the x direction.
1285    * @param {Number} ty The amount to translate in the y direction.
1286    * @return A matrix transformation representing a translation by tx and ty.
1287    * @type Matrix
1288   */
1289   Matrix.translation = function(tx, ty) {
1290     return Matrix(1, 0, 0, 1, tx, ty);
1291   };
1292   /***
1293    * A constant representing the identity matrix.
1294    * @name IDENTITY
1295    * @fieldOf Matrix
1296   */
1297   Matrix.IDENTITY = Matrix();
1298   /***
1299    * A constant representing the horizontal flip transformation matrix.
1300    * @name HORIZONTAL_FLIP
1301    * @fieldOf Matrix
1302   */
1303   Matrix.HORIZONTAL_FLIP = Matrix(-1, 0, 0, 1);
1304   /***
1305    * A constant representing the vertical flip transformation matrix.
1306    * @name VERTICAL_FLIP
1307    * @fieldOf Matrix
1308   */
1309   Matrix.VERTICAL_FLIP = Matrix(1, 0, 0, -1);
1310   window["Point"] = Point;
1311   return (window["Matrix"] = Matrix);

1402 /***
1403  * A mod method useful for array wrapping. The range of the function is
1404  * constrained to remain in bounds of array indices.
1405  *
1406  * <pre>
1407  * Example:
1408  * (-1).mod(5) === 4
1409  * </pre>
1410  *
1411  * @param {Number} base
1412  * @returns An integer between 0 and (base - 1) if base is positive.
1413  * @type Number
1414 */
1415 Number.prototype.mod = function(base) {
1416   var result;
1417   result = this % base;
1418   if (result < 0 && base > 0) {
1419     result += base;
1420   }
1421   return result;
1422 };
1423 /***

1425  * @type Number
1426  * @returns The sign of this number, 0 if the number is 0.
1427 */
1428 Number.prototype.sign = function() {
1429   if (this > 0) {
1430     return 1;
1431   } else if (this < 0) {
1432     return -1;
1433   } else {
1434     return 0;
1435   }
1436 };
1437 /***
1438  * Calls iterator the specified number of times, passing in the number of the
1439  * current iteration as a parameter: 0 on first call, 1 on the second call, etc.
1440  *
1441  * @param {Function} iterator The iterator takes a single parameter, the number
1442  * of the current iteration.
1443  * @param {Object} [context] The optional context parameter specifies an object
1444  * to treat as <code>this</code> in the iterator block.
1445  *
1446  * @returns The number of times the iterator was called.
1447  * @type Number
1448 */
1449 Number.prototype.times = function(iterator, context) {
1450   var i;
1451   i = -1;
1452   while (++i < this) {
1453     iterator.call(context, i);
1454   }
1455   return i;
1456 };
1457 /***
1458  * Returns the the nearest grid resolution less than or equal to the number.
1459  *
1460  *   EX:
1461  *    (7).snap(8) => 0
1462  *    (4).snap(8) => 0
1463  *    (12).snap(8) => 8
1464  *
1465  * @param {Number} resolution The grid resolution to snap to.
1466  * @returns The nearest multiple of resolution lower than the number.
1467  * @type Number
1468 */
1469 Number.prototype.snap = function(resolution) {
1470   var n;
1471   n = this / resolution;
1472   1 / 1;
1473   return n.floor() * resolution;
1474 };

1489 Number.prototype.approachRotation = function(target, maxDelta) {
1490   while (target > this + Math.PI) {
1491     target -= Math.TAU;
1492   }
1493   while (target < this - Math.PI) {
1494     target += Math.TAU;
1495   }
1496   return (target - this).clamp(-maxDelta, maxDelta) + this;
1497 };

1501 Number.prototype.constrainRotation = function() {

1505     target -= Math.TAU;
1506   }
1507   while (target < -Math.PI) {
1508     target += MATH.TAU;
1509   }
1510   return target;

3499 var CellularAutomata;
3500 CellularAutomata = function(I) {
3501   var currentState, get, neighbors, nextState, self;
3502   I || (I = {});
3503   $.reverseMerge(I, {
3504     cellUpdate: function(row, col, value, neighbors) {
3505       var neighborCounts;
3506       neighborCounts = neighbors.sum();
3507       return +((value + neighborCounts) >= 5);
3508     },
3509     initializeCell: function(row, col) {
3510       return rand() < 0.45;
3511     },
3512     outsideValue: function(row, col) {
3513       return 1;
3514     },
3515     width: 32,
3516     height: 32
3517   });
3518   currentState = [];
3519   nextState = [];
3520   get = function(row, col) {
3521     if (((0 <= row) && (row < I.height)) && ((0 <= col) && (col < I.width))) {
3522       return currentState[row][col];
3523     } else {
3524       return I.outsideValue(row, col);
3525     }
3526   };
3527   neighbors = function(row, col) {
3528     return [get(row - 1, col - 1), get(row - 1, col), get(row - 1, col + 1), get(row, col - 1), get(row, col + 1), get(row + 1, col - 1), get(row + 1, col), get(row + 1, col + 1)];
3529   };
3530   I.height.times(function(row) {
3531     currentState[row] = [];
3532     return I.width.times(function(col) {
3533       return (currentState[row][col] = I.initializeCell(row, col));
3534     });
3535   });
3536   self = {
3537     data: function() {
3538       return currentState;
3539     },
3540     get: function(row, col) {
3541       return currentState[row][col];
3542     },
3543     update: function(updateFn) {
3544       I.height.times(function(row) {
3545         return (nextState[row] = currentState[row].map(function(value, col) {
3546           return updateFn ? updateFn(row, col, value, neighbors(row, col)) : I.cellUpdate(row, col, value, neighbors(row, col));
3547         }));
3548       });
3549       currentState = nextState;
3550       return (nextState = []);
3551     }
3552   };
3553   return self;
3554 };;
3555 var Collidable;
3556 Collidable = function(I) {
3557   I || (I = {});
3558   return {
3559     solid_collision: function(other) {
3560       if (other.solid && other.bounds) {
3561         if (Collision.rectangular(self, other)) {
3562           self.trigger('collision');
3563           return other.trigger('collision');
3564         }
3565       }
3566     },
3567     collides_with: function(other) {
3568       var nearby, quadTree;
3569       if (other.solid && other.bounds) {
3570         if (Object.isArray(other)) {
3571           quadTree = QuadTree();
3572           other.each(function(collidable) {
3573             return quadTree.insert(collidable);
3574           });
3575           nearby = quadTree.retrieve(self);
3576           return nearby.each(function(close_collider) {
3577             return self.solid_collision(close_collider);
3578           });
3579         } else {
3580           return solid_collision(other);
3581         }
3582       }
3583     }

3586 var Collision;
3587 /***
3588 Collision holds many methods useful for checking geometric overlap of various objects.
3589 
3590 @name Collision
3591 @namespace
3592 */
3593 Collision = {
3594   rectangular: function(a, b) {
3595     return a.x < b.x + b.width && a.x + a.width > b.x && a.y < b.y + b.height && a.y + a.height > b.y;
3596   },
3597   circular: function(a, b) {
3598     var dx, dy, r;
3599     r = a.radius + b.radius;
3600     dx = b.x - a.x;
3601     dy = b.y - a.y;
3602     return r * r >= dx * dx + dy * dy;
3603   },
3604   rayCircle: function(source, direction, target) {
3605     var dt, hit, intersection, intersectionToTarget, intersectionToTargetLength, laserToTarget, projection, projectionLength, radius;
3606     radius = target.radius();
3607     target = target.position();
3608     laserToTarget = target.subtract(source);
3609     projectionLength = direction.dot(laserToTarget);
3610     if (projectionLength < 0) {
3611       return false;
3612     }
3613     projection = direction.scale(projectionLength);
3614     intersection = source.add(projection);
3615     intersectionToTarget = target.subtract(intersection);
3616     intersectionToTargetLength = intersectionToTarget.length();
3617     if (intersectionToTargetLength < radius) {
3618       hit = true;
3619     }
3620     if (hit) {
3621       dt = Math.sqrt(radius * radius - intersectionToTargetLength * intersectionToTargetLength);
3622       return (hit = direction.scale(projectionLength - dt).add(source));
3623     }
3624   },
3625   rayRectangle: function(source, direction, target) {
3626     var areaPQ0, areaPQ1, hit, p0, p1, t, tX, tY, xval, xw, yval, yw;
3627     xw = target.xw;
3628     yw = target.yw;
3629     if (source.x < target.x) {
3630       xval = target.x - xw;
3631     } else {
3632       xval = target.x + xw;
3633     }
3634     if (source.y < target.y) {
3635       yval = target.y - yw;
3636     } else {
3637       yval = target.y + yw;
3638     }
3639     if (direction.x === 0) {
3640       p0 = Point(target.x - xw, yval);
3641       p1 = Point(target.x + xw, yval);
3642       t = (yval - source.y) / direction.y;
3643     } else if (direction.y === 0) {
3644       p0 = Point(xval, target.y - yw);
3645       p1 = Point(xval, target.y + yw);
3646       t = (xval - source.x) / direction.x;
3647     } else {
3648       tX = (xval - source.x) / direction.x;
3649       tY = (yval - source.y) / direction.y;
3650       if ((tX < tY || ((-xw < source.x - target.x) && (source.x - target.x < xw))) && !((-yw < source.y - target.y) && (source.y - target.y < yw))) {
3651         p0 = Point(target.x - xw, yval);
3652         p1 = Point(target.x + xw, yval);
3653         t = tY;
3654       } else {
3655         p0 = Point(xval, target.y - yw);
3656         p1 = Point(xval, target.y + yw);
3657         t = tX;
3658       }
3659     }
3660     if (t > 0) {
3661       areaPQ0 = direction.cross(p0.subtract(source));
3662       areaPQ1 = direction.cross(p1.subtract(source));
3663       return areaPQ0 * areaPQ1 < 0 ? (hit = direction.scale(t).add(source)) : null;
3664     }
3665   }
3666 };;

3772               piecesRemaining.shift();

3774             } else {
3775               break;
3776                 ;//NOOP
3777             }
3778           }
3779           
3780           pageCharCount += currentLine.length;
3781           
3782           canvas.fillText(currentLine, textStart.x, textStart.y + line * I.lineHeight);
3783           lineWidth = canvas.measureText(currentLine);
3784           
3785           if(line * I.lineHeight < I.textHeight) {
3786             line += 1;
3787           } else {
3788             pageOffset += pageCharCount + line;
3789             line = 0;
3790             pageCharCount = 0;
3791             displayChars = 0;
3792             break;
3793               ;
3794           }
3795         }
3796         
3797         if(cursorOn && I.cursor) {
3798           canvas.fillRect(textStart.x + lineWidth, textStart.y + (line - 2) *I.lineHeight, I.cursorWidth, I.lineHeight);
3799         }
3800       });
3801       
3802     },
3803     
3804     flush: function() {
3805       displayChars = I.text.length;
3806     },
3807

3810       displayChars = 0;
3811       I.text = text;
3812     },
3813

3816       blinkCount += 1;

3819         blinkCount = 0;
3820         cursorOn = !cursorOn;
3821       }
3822     }

4174     return selector.split(",").invoke("trim");

4176   process: function(item) {
4177     var result;

4179     if (result) {
4180       if (result[4]) {
4181         result[4] = result[4].parse();
4182       }
4183       return result.splice(1);
4184     } else {
4185       return [];

4187   },
4188   generate: function(selector) {
4189     var ATTR, ATTR_VALUE, ID, TYPE, components;
4190     components = Engine.Selector.parse(selector).map(function(piece) {
4191       return Engine.Selector.process(piece);
4192     });
4193     TYPE = 0;
4194     ID = 1;
4195     ATTR = 2;
4196     ATTR_VALUE = 3;
4197     return {
4198       match: function(object) {
4199         var _i, _len, _ref, _ref2, attr, attrMatch, component, idMatch, typeMatch, value;
4200         _ref = components;
4201         for (_i = 0, _len = _ref.length; _i < _len; _i++) {
4202           component = _ref[_i];
4203           idMatch = (component[ID] === object.I.id) || !component[ID];
4204           typeMatch = (component[TYPE] === object.I["class"]) || !component[TYPE];
4205           if (attr = component[ATTR]) {
4206             if (typeof (_ref2 = (value = component[ATTR_VALUE])) !== "undefined" && _ref2 !== null) {
4207               attrMatch = (object.I[attr] === value);
4208             } else {
4209               attrMatch = object.I[attr];

4211           } else {
4212             attrMatch = true;
4213           }
4214           if (idMatch && typeMatch && attrMatch) {
4215             return true;
4216           }
4217         }
4218         return false;
4219       }

4460         currentChar = chars.shift();
4461         text[line - 1].push(currentChar);
4462         return Game.canvas.measureText(stringLine(line)) > I.width - I.padding * 2 ? addLine() : null;
4463       }
4464     }

4468   function LoaderProxy() {
4469     return {
4470       draw: $.noop,
4471       fill: $.noop,
4472       frame: $.noop,
4473       update: $.noop,
4474       width: null,
4475       height: null
4476     };
4477   }
4478   
4479   function Sprite(image, sourceX, sourceY, width, height) {
4480     sourceX = sourceX || 0;
4481     sourceY = sourceY || 0;
4482     width = width || image.width;
4483     height = height || image.height;
4484     
4485     return {
4486       draw: function(canvas, x, y) {
4487         canvas.drawImage(
4488           image,
4489           sourceX,
4490           sourceY,
4491           width,
4492           height,
4493           x,
4494           y,
4495           width,
4496           height
4497         );
4498       },
4499       
4500       fill: function(canvas, x, y, width, height, repeat) {
4501         repeat = repeat || "repeat";
4502         var pattern = canvas.createPattern(image, repeat);
4503         canvas.fillColor(pattern);
4504         canvas.fillRect(x, y, width, height);
4505       },
4506       
4507       width: width,
4508       height: height
4509     };
4510   };
4511   
4512   Sprite.load = function(url, loadedCallback) {
4513     var img = new Image();
4514     var proxy = LoaderProxy();
4515     
4516     img.onload = function() {
4517       var tile = Sprite(this);
4518       
4519       $.extend(proxy, tile);
4520       
4521       if(loadedCallback) {
4522         loadedCallback(proxy);
4523       }
4524     };
4525     
4526     img.src = url;
4527     
4528     return proxy;
4529   };

4534     return Sprite.load(pixieSpriteImagePath + id + "/original.png", callback);

4543         warn("Could not find sprite named: '" + name + "' in App.");
4544       }
4545     } else {
4546       // Treat name as URL
4547       return window.Sprite.fromURL(name, callback);

4555   var Map, fromPixieId;
4556   Map = function(data, entityCallback) {
4557     var loadEntities, spriteLookup, tileHeight, tileWidth;
4558     tileHeight = data.tileHeight;
4559     tileWidth = data.tileWidth;
4560     spriteLookup = {};
4561     data.tileset.each(function(tileData, i) {
4562       return (spriteLookup[i] = Sprite.fromURL(tileData.src));
4563     });
4564     loadEntities = function() {
4565       if (!(entityCallback)) {
4566         return null;
4567       }
4568       return data.layers.each(function(layer, layerIndex) {
4569         if (!(layer.name.match(/entities/i))) {
4570           return null;
4571         }
4572         return layer.tiles.each(function(row, y) {
4573           return row.each(function(tileIndex, x) {
4574             var entityData;
4575             if (spriteLookup[tileIndex]) {
4576               entityData = $.extend({
4577                 layer: layerIndex,
4578                 sprite: spriteLookup[tileIndex],
4579                 tileIndex: tileIndex,
4580                 x: x * tileWidth,
4581                 y: y * tileHeight
4582               }, data.tileset[tileIndex] == null ? undefined : data.tileset[tileIndex].properties);
4583               return entityCallback(entityData);
4584             }
4585           });
4586         });
4587       });
4588     };
4589     loadEntities();
4590     return $.extend(data, {
4591       draw: function(canvas, x, y) {
4592         return canvas.withTransform(Matrix.translation(x, y), function() {
4593           return data.layers.each(function(layer) {
4594             if (layer.name.match(/entities/i)) {
4595               return null;
4596             }
4597             return layer.tiles.each(function(row, y) {
4598               return row.each(function(tileIndex, x) {
4599                 var sprite;
4600                 return (sprite = spriteLookup[tileIndex]) ? sprite.draw(canvas, x * tileWidth, y * tileHeight) : null;
4601               });
4602             });
4603           });
4604         });
4605       }
4606     });
4607   };

4611   fromPixieId = function(id, callback, entityCallback) {
4612     var proxy, url;
4613     url = ("http://pixie.strd6.com/s3/tilemaps/" + (id) + "/data.json");
4614     proxy = {
4615       draw: $.noop
4616     };
4617     $.getJSON(url, function(data) {
4618       $.extend(proxy, Map(data, entityCallback));
4619       return (typeof callback === "function" ? callback(proxy) : undefined);
4620     });
4621     return proxy;
4622   };
